cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialogue generation. Additionally, the use of neural networks and adversarial learning techniques suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of sentiment labels and the focus on controlling sentiment in the generated responses suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Sound).
